# Checked-in async-profiler `collapsed` fixture for the
# `topo profile trace --mode=async-profiler` e2e tests. async-profiler is
# a native agent the user installs per platform; this fixture stands in
# for its `-o collapsed` text so CTest never has to attach the agent.
#
# Format: Brendan-Gregg folded stack (frames root -> leaf, `;`-separated,
# trailing integer = sample count) with async-profiler's `-t` extension —
# the stack ROOT is the thread token `[<tid>] <thread-name>`. The
# converter lifts the numeric tid into the per-event `tid` field, drops
# the thread token from the stack, and groups samples by thread.
# Comment lines (#) and blank lines are skipped.
#
# Same logical workload as jfr_sample.ndjson so the wall/alloc views are
# comparable: thread main (tid=1) and worker-0 (tid=42).
# Total samples: 4 + 2 + 2 + 3 + 1 = 12 across 5 unique stacks.
# `geom/Mesh.compute` appears in 9 / 12 samples.
[1] main;main/App.run;geom/Mesh.compute 4
[1] main;main/App.run;geom/Mesh.compute;geom/Mesh.normalize 2
[1] main;main/App.run;io/Writer.flush 2
[42] worker-0;main/Pool.work;geom/Mesh.compute 3
[42] worker-0;main/Pool.work;io/Writer.flush 1
